<section xml:id="section-nonexistent-limits">
    <title>Non-existent Limits</title>

    <p>Many limit values do not exist. Sometimes the non-existence is caused by the function value either increasing without bound or decreasing without bound. In these special cases we use the symbols <m>\infty</m> and <m>-\infty</m> to communicate the non-existence of the limits. <xref autoname="plural" ref="figure-first-nonexistent-limit"/><ndash/><xref autoname="no" ref="figure-last-nonexistent-limit"/> can be used to illustrate some ways in which we communicate the <term>non-existence</term> of these types of limits.</p>

    <ul>
        <li>In <xref ref="figure-first-nonexistent-limit"/> we could (correctly) write<br /><m>\lim\limits_{x\to2}\fe{k}{x}=\infty</m>, <m>\lim\limits_{x\to2^{-}}\fe{k}{x}=\infty</m>, and <m>\lim\limits_{x\to2^{+}}\fe{k}{x}=\infty</m>.</li>
       <li>In <xref ref="figure-middle-nonexistent-limit"/> we could (correctly) write<br /><m>\lim\limits_{t\to4}\fe{w}{t}=-\infty</m>, <m>\lim\limits_{t\to4^{-}}\fe{w}{t}=-\infty</m>, and <m>\lim\limits_{t\to4^{+}}\fe{w}{t}=-\infty</m>.</li>
       <li>In <xref ref="figure-last-nonexistent-limit"/> we could (correctly) write<br /><m>\lim\limits_{x\to-3^{-}}\fe{T}{x}=\infty</m> and <m>\lim\limits_{x\to-3^{+}}\fe{T}{x}=-\infty</m>.<br /> There is no shorthand way of communicating the non-existence of the two sided limit <m>\lim\limits_{x\to-3}\fe{T}{x}</m>.</li>
    </ul>

